Stakeholder Brief: Retail Performance Declinee Analysis
Prep for CEO | Analytics Team | 18-Month Review


1.Declining Repeat Customer Visits
(a) Returning customers are visiting less frequently, shrinking the active customer base.
(b) Key Business Questions: Which customers stopped returning? When did visits decline? What reactivation tactics work?
(c) Answers will inform targeted re-engagement campaign design and retention strategy.
(d) Customer transaction history and loyalty programme activity records are available.
(e) Segment of lapsed customers identified; 90-day re-engagement campaign proposal submitted.
2.Underperforming Product Categories
(a) Certain products consistently underperform across stores, reducing overall revenue.
(b) Key Business Questions: Which categories underperform? Are failures store-specific or company-wide? What should be discontinued?
(c) Answers will inform product ranging, stocking, and shelf allocation decisions.
(d) Product sales data and store performance records across all 30 stores are available.
(e) Bottom 20% product list with store-level discontinuation or repositioning recommendations submitted.
3.Loyalty Programme Not Converting to Sales
(a) Members are active in the programme but not completing purchases.
(b) Key Business Questions: Where is conversion lowest? Are reward thresholds too high? What triggers a purchase?
(c) Answers will inform loyalty programme restructuring and reward threshold adjustments.
(d) Loyalty activity, transaction records, and product sales data are available.
(e) Store-by-store conversion gap analysis with revised reward structure submitted.
4.Store-Level Performance Gaps
(a) Underperforming stores are dragging down company-wide results unaddressed.
(b) Key Business Questions: Which 5 stores perform worst? When did decline begin? What caused it?
(c) Answers will inform individualised store targets and intervention plans.
(d) Store performance, product sales, and customer transaction data are available.
(e) Bottom 5 stores identified with individual monthly targets and decline timelines submitted.
5.High Transactions, Low Revenue Per Visit
(a) Transaction volumes remain steady but spend per visit is falling.
(b) Key Business Questions: Which stores show declining basket size? When did it drop? What products are affected?
(c) Answers will inform point-of-sale upselling and complementary product strategies.
(d) Transaction records, product sales, and store performance data are available.
(e) Monthly average transaction value analysis with point-of-sale strategy recommendations submitted.
